# UI copy: Title Case for buttons and titles

## Default

Use **Title Case** (capitalize the first letter of each major word) for:

- **Buttons** — e.g. `Save Changes`, `Add User`, `Back To Home`, `Log Out`, `Delete`, `Cancel`
- **Page titles** — `<h1>`, visible page headings, and browser title segments (e.g. `Users / Shore Reporting`)
- **Modal / dialog titles** — e.g. `Edit Role`, `Delete Department`
- **Primary section headings** that act like titles (e.g. card headers)

## Examples

| Avoid | Prefer |
|-------|--------|
| Save changes | Save Changes |
| Add user | Add User |
| Back to home | Back To Home |
| Edit profile | Edit Profile |

## Exceptions

- **Short actions** of one word stay capitalized: `Cancel`, `Close`, `Submit`, `Delete`
- **Acronyms** stay uppercase: `API`, `ID`, `CSV`
- **Brand / product names** as intended: `Shore Reporting`
- **Sentence-style** body copy, placeholders, helper text, and long descriptions are **not** required to be Title Case
- **`aria-label`** and tooltips that are full sentences may use sentence case if clearer

When adding or editing buttons or title-level UI strings in Vue, Blade, or routes meta titles, apply this rule unless an exception applies.
